OL,3,CWoman appears in court charged with
OL,4,Cmanslaughter of four paddleboarders
OL,6,FEmergency services attended the scene,
OL,7,Fwhere Mr O'Dwyer, from Port Talbot, Ms
OL,8,FRogers, from Merthyr Tydfil, and Ms
OL,9,FWheatley, from Swansea, were declared
OL,10,Fdead.
OL,12,FMs Powell, from Bridgend, was taken to
OL,13,Fnearby Withybush Hospital but died six
OL,14,Fdays later.
OL,16,FLloyd was charged with five offences
OL,17,Frelating to the incident on 4 October
OL,18,Fthis year.
